Scott Shirley, his wife Mayo and seven-year-old son Phoenix were travelling back to Washington DC after a birthday trip to Disney World, Orlando .
They discovered the bags to be wet with vomit on the floor of the plane .
The family were told by cabin crew that a passenger on an earlier flight had been sick in the seating area, and that staff had cleaned the area before take-off .
Mr Shirley said: 'I immediately had a feeling of panic on my face and loudly pronounced it to be vomit'